<subSubSection id="D44B9285EFA512D64BEC25EBA35A18C4" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B80330282EA8617BBFE5BCDAA14F17B6" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4E27D7EB2D9014E560F935E99FE9CE36" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="5698C60DE4FA6F5383EE5B4DAAA7306A" authorityName="Bordera &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Piasites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Piasites nigricollis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricollis">
<emphasis id="D04051F1AF52A9079A0A1581FE906901" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Piasites nigricollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="3985BECD7B2D430EACC16CC2D119422A" authorityName="Seyrig" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Piasites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Piasites" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B6525539350D67EBD2269385A04702F6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Piasites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the combination of the following characters: pronotum shallowly and longitudinally strigose, ventrally smooth (Figs 
<figureCitation id="3407E35EB36BDF49E5CB05DBC29EE849" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Piasites nigricollis sp. nov., female (holotype): A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head and mesoscutum, dorsal view E metasoma, dorsal view F front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, E); 0.3 mm (B, D, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677624" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">6C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="76D93C38C78CEE76AACC207A00A7E65E" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13D</figureCitation>
); mesoscutum evenly convex, mostly smooth and shiny with fine punctures on median lobe (Figs 
<figureCitation id="E434C3104AE039198BAF940F89AA7BE7" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Piasites nigricollis sp. nov., female (holotype): A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head and mesoscutum, dorsal view E metasoma, dorsal view F front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, E); 0.3 mm (B, D, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677624" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">6C, D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="63C5820A9CB3DC612EF42C2C05E45C6E" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13D</figureCitation>
); mesopleuron mostly smooth and shiny, shallowly rugulose punctate at dorsal anterior corner, ventral anterior part shallowly punctate (Figs 
<figureCitation id="7DCD58410C7CFC83166C190EA0E36F92" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Piasites nigricollis sp. nov., female (holotype): A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head and mesoscutum, dorsal view E metasoma, dorsal view F front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, E); 0.3 mm (B, D, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677624" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">6C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="595E8CFA2E823443025663E9AFD58F70" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13D</figureCitation>
); propodeum strongly rugose punctate (Figs 
<figureCitation id="18E26C79EB2515E84FA5F7D28E2E3C40" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Propodeum of Piasites, dorsal view, females (II): A P. nigricollis sp. nov. (holotype) B P. orbitalis sp. nov. (holotype) C P. lineatus sp. nov. (paratype) D P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677619" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2AA69739A2D3DC82502F6AAE68D437A3" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13D</figureCitation>
); propleuron, anterior part of pronotum and mesoscutum brownish black, ocular orbits completely white cream (Figs 
<figureCitation id="675B3B9A3EDCAD95E3E2F4C9D2250F61" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Piasites nigricollis sp. nov., female (holotype): A habitus, lateral view B head, front view C head and mesosoma, lateral view D head and mesoscutum, dorsal view E metasoma, dorsal view F front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, E); 0.3 mm (B, D, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677624" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">6C, D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="64B5A9430DBCF47DAA4A710C238C1C82" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13D</figureCitation>
). Additionally, male with metapleuron smooth to shallowly rugulose punctate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="369D8CCDD7877232FC0AD2F0E3706109" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Piasites species, males A-E head and mesosoma, lateral view: A P. carinatus B P. quasimodus sp. nov. (paratype) C P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype) D P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) E P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype) F-G metapleuron: F P. nigricollis sp. nov. (paratype) G P. perinetensis sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-E); 0.2 mm (F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677631" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">13F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
